  "text": "We first identified sperm GSK3 as an enzyme involved in activation of PPP1CC2 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This activation was thought to involve phosphorylation of the protein phosphatase inhibitor PPP1R2 (inhibitor I-2) by GSK3. To determine if there was a relationship between GSK3A and protein phosphatase, we assayed for protein phosphatase activity in sperm from Gsk3a À/À mice. Protein phosphatase activity was measured using phosphorylase a as a substrate. Data in Figure 6B show that total protein phosphatase (PP1 þ PP2A; Fig. 6A ) and PP1 activities (Fig. 6B ) in both the soluble and insoluble fractions of sperm sonicates from Gsk3a À/À mice were significantly higher than in WT mice.",
